Back Day 💪

This was my last workout right before my neck injury. I felt like I was making so much progress. 

I was never able to do a lat pull down without pain unless it was a very light load, and this day I was finally able to incorporate a heavier load than usual with no pain. 

It’s not uncommon to make progress and then go backwards. The road to achieving our dreams isn’t always pretty and a straight line going up, but if it’s worth it we keep going despite the set backs. Like my boy @schwarzenegger once said, “I’ll be back” 😎
.
I haven’t trained since this day, and I’m looking forward to slowly start up again in a week or 2 and test the waters. In the meantime, train for me 💪😎
.
Swipe to the end to see my warmup and my post workout meal @nugonutrition the best dam protein bar on planet earth 🌍 code: EHALEN20 to save 20% 🥳
.

I have obviously lost some muscle mass not training for over a month now. I still have to flex like I’m so swole though because one day I will be 😎

My current body weight is 115lbs. I believe the last time I weighed that much I was a junior in high school cutting weight for a wrestling 🤼‍♀️ tournament 😂

I’m really just anticipating being able to burn energy again! I’m gonna run like a dog that just got let out of it’s cage with a wagging tail and all the joy 😆

Clip 1,2…,or ? 😂

So many questions regarding my neck, I’ll answer briefly for those concerned. 

I’m taking gabapentin, pregablin, and diclofenec to make just daily living not so uncomfortable. I still have nerve pain and it happens at the most unpredictable moments. 

I see a neurosurgeon August 4th and now I’m just waiting. I understand these medications won’t heal me but in the meantime, they are a huge help. 

Despite my present condition, I won’t stop being active. Walking is about all I can do and my occasional silly flexing. I am still enjoying life even though what I love the most (Olympic weightlifting/just lifting heavy shit well) is not permitted at the moment. 

Stay strong 💪 & I hope you guys had the best dam Fourth of July weekend 🥳

Finally LEFT LOS ANGELES 🙌
.
I was born and raised in LA and never. Ever. Left. I mean why would I? It has a beautiful beach, the weather is great, and trainers get paid well there. Clips 5&6 are reasons why I’ll miss LA and its unique toxic beauty. 

But to be honest, I was sick of living in DTLA, sick of the traffic, and the homeless drug addicts. Not to mention the ridiculous riots/protests that go on constantly. The last clip was my morning walk to get coffee #nothanks 😅
.
So it’s time I take a break, September 1st I packed the U-Haul with my Jeep and made an 8hour drive during the floods to move to Vegas. Idk how long I’ll stay here since I’m realizing trainers make pennies here, but I’m gonna give it a shot. 

When I got here, I felt relief being away from that constant go, go, go, LA anxiety. I get to zen out and stretch out in my nice apartment gym - stoked I still have my middle splits ☺️👌
.

There is a force called life which is greater than us, it’s completely out of our control, and it’s doing its own thing. It doesn’t care about our plans, goals, or dreams.. or your organs 😜

I just moved to Vegas looking to build my career here as a personal trainer and to start a new life here, but my appendix says 👎 … Not now at least! 

Doctors orders: Rest for 5 weeks in a city where you know maybe 2 people that would help a tad and with no work. &Good luck Liz 🍀 

However, the brightside is that our power lies in how we choose to respond to these experiences life hands over. 

Despite the physical pain and the obvious inconveniences of not being able to train, work, live, or sleep comfortably, I decided to relax and just be here with the situation and let it take place. 

Honor it, respect the fact that I am still alive. Thankful for the strength I have to deal with it, remain open, and embrace it with all my heart and soul. 

Life isn’t just about having the strength to lift heavy weights (actually it is) but being strong in heart and in soul (but more importantly in the gym) 🤣 

All jokes aside, the gym/sports is what fires 🔥 me up like no other, and this little situation here is making me more fired up to come back stronger than ever. If I get pulled back again, I’ll get up and try again and again… and again, and again. 

Dare to be different and enjoy ALL OF LIFE! Don’t just post your ass on IG, go that extra mile and share appendix surgeries 😉😂#stayreal

Where to begin!? 😅 
 
As some of you may know, I had a chiropractic accident that left me in a lot of nerve pain with an additional 3 extra disc injuries. 

Following that incident, my doctor prescribed me all kinds of medications. The only one I took out of desperation to help with the pain was gabapentin. The gabapentin was really messing up my speech and I was slurring my words a lot, I stopped taking it.

Now I was left with no medication and nerve pain, so I looked into natural ways to reduce inflammation. So, in June 25,2023 I decided to give the CARNIVORE Diet a shot to help me.

And I absolutely loved it! Every time I had a steak in front of me I could almost cry tears of joy 🥲 Unfortunately, my body didn’t respond well (3months of diarrhea) and I kept hoping my body would adjust. I was stubborn and refused to eat a carb or a vegetable. 

Then, one morning Sept 16th after just moving to Vegas, my appendix got infected and had “stones” aka diarrhea and had to get rushed to the hospital for surgery. (Check out previous post) 

After that day, I realized what a mistake I made 😅 I started incorporating veggies and the diarrhea immediately stopped and now I’m on a journey to restore my gut health, since this carnivore diet really messed it for me. 

I want to mention that I actually liked the diet,  and I messaged these IG famous Carnivore pages asking for help/advice and none of them responded. One of them, Laura Spath, must have hated my story so much she blocked me. 😂 

All the other ones flat out ignored me except one Dr. Berry but he mainly wanted to use my platform to promote the diet, in which I said I’m not ready to promote anything to my followers until I try it and see how it goes first because I want to give honest feedback. 

Here it is, honest feedback and now that you know the risks involved, you can approach it more cautiously than I did. 

In the meantime, I’m using @viome to help restore my gut health. I sent in my poop, saliva, and blood samples and now we are slowly making progress. If you guys are interested as well, use CODE: HALEN to save $110 on your Full Intelligence Test 😎
.

Protein Cinnamon Loaf 🍞

🔸1/2 Tsp Baking Soda

🔸2 Tsp Cinnamon + Pop Corn Seasoning
